• The creation of a data-tracking system that provides an early warning if the state needs to reinstate a stay-at-home order.
Key to Newsom’s strategy for reopening the state is dramatically increasing access to coronavirus testing and building up public health resources so new cases can be quickly identified and contained before they spark another outbreak.
Bay Area health officials imposed their own stay-at-home order three days before Newsom issued his statewide directive.